<h4 id="definition">Definition</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Euler Trail: A trail that traverses every edge of G is called an Euler trail
of G.</li>
  <li>Tour: A tour of G is a closed walk that traverses each edge of G at least
once.</li>
  <li>Euler Tour: An Euler tour is a tour which traverses each edge exactly once.</li>
  <li>Hamilton path: A path that contains every vertex of G is called a Hamilton
path of G.</li>
  <li>Hamilton cycle: a Hamilton cycle of G is a cycle that contain every vertex of
G.</li>
  <li>Hamiltonian: A graph is hamiltonian if it contains a Hamilton cycle.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="application-chinese-postman-problem">Application: Chinese Postman Problem</h4>
<p>A postman picks up mail at the post office, delivers it, and then returns to the
post office. He must of course, cover each street in his area at least once.</p>
<ul>
  <li>subject to this condition, he wishes to choose his route in such a way that he
walks as little as possible.
